com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.rmi.test

Class TestMultiSessionRmi

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.rmi.server.RemoteObject
      • java.rmi.server.RemoteServer
        • java.rmi.server.UnicastRemoteObject
          • com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.rmi.test.TestMultiSessionRmi
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFixListener, Serializable, Remote, EventListener

    public class TestMultiSessionRmi
extends UnicastRemoteObject
implements IFixListener
    Sample Catalys RMI Client application which creates and sends a few messages to multiple RMI sessions. The Sender and Target Comp IDs of the session are obtained automatically, by querying the Catalys Server RMI Application.

    Command Line Args:

    • Catalys RMI Server Application URL (//[<host>][:<port>]/<name>). Required.

    This class also acts as a listener to FIX events coming over RMI from the Catalys Server, by extending UnicastRemoteObject and implementing the IFixListener interface. Alternately, it can be a normal Java "main" object and create a separate object as a listener. Then only that listener object has to extend UnicastRemoteObject and implement IFixListener.
